stylometry: We used clustering as a data mining method.  I used clustering in my own problem by gathering information about 15 players on the cleveland indians.  I gathered their statistics in spring training up to certain date.  I used games played, at bats, hits, home runs, rbi, and batting average.  I entered in all of the data then I entered in formulas in the following columns that organized this information and gave me a number or result for each player based on the performance of other players.  The goal of clustering this information was to assign players into groups or clusters who performed and played at the same level based on the six categories I entered the data for.  Just looking at the data one might think that a batting average is very high and the player is doing good, but clustering will determine if the player is performing the best or how well he is performing by taking into consideration all of the other information added into the table and using the other players as a model too.
